<h4 id="foreword">Foreword</h4>
<p>This post addresses <a href="octra.org">Octra</a>, a cryptocurrency
which claims to provide <a
href="https://wikipedia.org/wiki/Homomorphic_encryption">fully-homomorphic
encryption</a> (FHE) via a new methodology–dubbed HFHE (hypergraph FHE).
As a result of such curiosities, we dug. Though, when digging, this
rotten stench permeated everything related to Octra that we dug into.
For better or for worse, we kept digging. This post is the result of
such.</p>
<p>Kirill, David, Lambda, whatever you want us to call you. If you’re
going to play the “pseudonymous cryptowiz,” you need to at least have
half-decent OpSec. You didn’t. So sit back and enjoy.</p>
<p>All information in this post was obtained by means of OSINT.
Everything here is legal.</p>
<p>After realising that the soundness-by-obscurity Octra deployed
dissuaded people from speaking on this for some time, we’ve chosen to
include TLDRs explaining the “difficult” parts. Do not take them as the
totality of that section.</p>
<h5 id="updated">Updated!!!!</h5>
<p>Thanks for scrolling slightly more. As of writing this, it is 16:00
UTC, 04.07.2026.</p>
<p>Before I get on with anything else, please note that this would not
have been possible without the amazing people who assisted in our
investigation. Kypwny had produced earlier work on Octra and proceeded
to assist a tad with the update. Someone from <a
href="https://int.pl">int.pl</a> let us know we missed some stuff. And,
lastly, there were two sources which both asked to be known only as
anonymous sources. These two provided us with far more background on
Kirill than we knew existed. They singlehandedly (doublehandedly?)
expanded Kirill’s section to a far greater extent. This includes proving
with 100% certainty that Kirill is David. Thank you all so much.</p>
